    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter May 2nd with a high-ceiling lineup led by **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (72.34) and **Junior Caminero** (67.10). **Pete Crow-Armstrong** is our premier play today, benefiting from a +14% dynamic platoon boost against Ryne Nelson, whose SP_xERA of 4.23 suggests a favorable environment for **Pete Crow-Armstrong** to leverage his speed. Similarly, **Junior Caminero** projects as a core building block batting second, where his +8% order bonus and positive platoon split against Landen Roupp position him for high-volume scoring opportunities. **Colt Keith** (66.91) remains a high-efficiency start, drawing extra value from his matchup against Kumar Rocker; the anticipated slow delivery from the mound provides a specific green light for **Colt Keith** to manufacture points via stolen base potential, a critical metric for our roster construction.\n\nWhile we are aggressive in our pursuit of efficiency, we are keeping a close watch on volatility. **Caleb Durbin** (63.88) provides an intriguing play due to his high stolen base floor, but his start is clouded by a 33% rain risk. We also have concerns regarding **Yordan Alvarez** (53.88); despite his elite 0.434 xwOBA, his score is suppressed by a difficult matchup against lefty Connelly Early and identical rain risk. The most difficult bench decision involved **Chase Meidroth** (47.06), who nearly cracked the lineup. Ultimately, the optimizer opted for the more specialized profiles of **Josh Smith** and **Luke Raley** to better balance our 5x5 categories, specifically seeking the platoon advantages that **Josh Smith** carries against Keider Montero. With **Christian Yelich** remaining sidelined on the IL, we continue to rely on the depth provided by **Lars Nootbaar**, **Zac Veen**, **Pedro Ramirez**, and **Luis Pena** to maintain our competitive edge as we await further roster clarity.",
